The end result is an engine that is both simpler and much faster. In the above example we run two different benchmarks. The first is a run of 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/blob/main/coloring/gradient.nu] this script
 in the Nushell script repo. The second is a tight processing loop over many 10 million small records: 
``echo 1..10000000 | prepend 777 | append 555 | where $it > 7 | length``
.
Though the performance numbers are still early, they're extremely promising.
